---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const faqData = [
  {
    question: "Does Costco hot dog have pork?",
    answer: "No. Costco hot dogs are 100% all-beef and contain no pork or pork by-products."
  },
  {
    question: "Are Costco hot dogs beef or pork?",
    answer: "They are 100% beef. Kirkland Signature hot dogs use USDA Choice beef only."
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Does Costco Hot Dog Have Pork?"
  description="No — Costco hot dogs are 100% all-beef. Full ingredient analysis confirming no pork content."
  type="faq"
  faqData={faqData}
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-8 text-center mb-10">
      <p class="text-sm text-green-700 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide">Answer</p>
      <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-green-800 mt-2">No</p>
      <p class="text-green-700 mt-2">100% beef, no pork</p>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Does Costco Hot Dog Have Pork?</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">A definitive answer based on official ingredient lists.</p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Official Ingredients</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Costco hot dogs are made by Kirkland Signature and list the following ingredients: Beef, water, salt, contains 2% or less of corn syrup, dextrose, flavorings, paprika, sodium erythorbate, sodium nitrite. There is no pork, poultry, or any meat other than beef.</p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Why People Ask</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Some cheaper hot dog brands use a mixture of meats including pork and chicken. Costco's commitment to 100% beef is part of what makes their hot dog a higher-quality option at an unbeatable price.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
